  "description": "A high-density scalp electroencephalogram (EEG) dataset acquired during sensorimotor rhythm-based brain-computer interface (BCI) tasks. The dataset contains recordings from multiple subjects performing motor imagery and related sensorimotor activities using high-density electrode configurations, designed to support the development and validation of BCI systems. This resource provides a comprehensive foundation for investigating neural correlates of motor control and advancing BCI technology. This NEMAR record represents the same dataset as OpenNeuro ds004447.",
